1
00:00:10,792 --> 00:00:13,795
<i>[valiant music]</i>

2
00:00:13,795 --> 00:00:20,844
<i>♪ ♪</i>

3
00:00:24,097 --> 00:00:27,267
DHIANEILA: Long, long ago,

4
00:00:27,267 --> 00:00:31,521
in a time
all but lost to memory,

5
00:00:31,521 --> 00:00:33,857
at the farthest reaches
of our universe,

6
00:00:33,857 --> 00:00:37,443
there dwelled a people
called the Golden Tribe.

7
00:00:37,443 --> 00:00:40,613
They, who possess
the power to create worlds

8
00:00:40,613 --> 00:00:42,907
and who knew the will of time,

9
00:00:42,907 --> 00:00:46,953
beckoned to the other tribes
spread out across the stars.

10
00:00:46,953 --> 00:00:53,084
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11
00:00:53,084 --> 00:00:58,131
And the great tribes
who answered their call were...

12
00:00:58,131 --> 00:01:00,842
the Silver Tribe...

13
00:01:04,721 --> 00:01:06,806
The Bronze Tribe...

14
00:01:08,808 --> 00:01:11,186
The Heroic Tribe...

15
00:01:15,148 --> 00:01:17,483
And the Iron Tribe.

16
00:01:22,864 --> 00:01:25,200
Later,
in their boundless wisdom,

17
00:01:25,200 --> 00:01:28,077
the Golden Tribe chose
to leave this universe

18
00:01:28,077 --> 00:01:29,913
for another.

19
00:01:31,873 --> 00:01:33,583
The Silver Tribe named itself

20
00:01:33,583 --> 00:01:36,002
the successor
to the Golden Tribe's position

21
00:01:36,002 --> 00:01:40,340
as the most powerful people
in the universe.

22
00:01:43,176 --> 00:01:45,845
These new rulers
looked upon the Iron Tribe,

23
00:01:45,845 --> 00:01:47,597
a weak race
in possession of the fifth

24
00:01:47,597 --> 00:01:50,016
and most powerful Nodos,

25
00:01:50,016 --> 00:01:51,643
as their mortal enemy

26
00:01:51,643 --> 00:01:53,645
and vowed to wipe them out.

27
00:01:53,645 --> 00:01:56,648
<i>["Gravitation" by Angela]</i>

28
00:01:56,648 --> 00:01:59,734
[woman singing in Japanese]

29
00:03:35,538 --> 00:03:36,789
TAIL: I don't know.

30
00:03:36,789 --> 00:03:38,499
Which one do you think
he'll like?

31
00:03:38,499 --> 00:03:40,501
MAIL:
Well, I think this one's cute.

32
00:03:40,501 --> 00:03:43,087
I mean, she's in her uniform.
Don't you think?

33
00:03:43,087 --> 00:03:44,505
TAIL: [groans]

34
00:03:44,505 --> 00:03:46,758
I don't know which one to pick!

35
00:03:46,758 --> 00:03:48,301
‐ This one'll cheer him up.

36
00:03:48,301 --> 00:03:50,428
He was pretty depressed,
you know.

37
00:03:50,428 --> 00:03:52,013
AGE: Dhianeila!

38
00:03:52,013 --> 00:03:53,848
<i>[lighthearted music]</i>

39
00:03:53,848 --> 00:03:54,974
BOTH: [scream]

40
00:03:54,974 --> 00:03:56,059
‐ What is it, Age?

41
00:03:56,059 --> 00:03:57,935
‐ Don't scare us like that!

42
00:03:57,935 --> 00:04:01,147
‐ What is that?
‐ Photo.

43
00:04:01,147 --> 00:04:02,565
[shutter snaps]

44
00:04:04,025 --> 00:04:05,985
[Age grunting]

45
00:04:05,985 --> 00:04:08,321
‐ Age!
‐ Hey, he did it again.

46
00:04:08,321 --> 00:04:11,741
‐ Yeah, he talks like a kid.

47
00:04:11,741 --> 00:04:13,242
‐ Not Age?

48
00:04:13,242 --> 00:04:14,994
‐ Say "me."
‐ You're 16.

49
00:04:14,994 --> 00:04:17,246
It sounds childish
when you refer to yourself

50
00:04:17,246 --> 00:04:19,499
by your name.

51
00:04:19,499 --> 00:04:21,334
‐ It's me?

52
00:04:46,692 --> 00:04:49,529
‐ I wish I had been born
a savage little monkey.

53
00:04:49,529 --> 00:04:50,947
‐ Don't be glum.

54
00:04:50,947 --> 00:04:53,866
‐ We're here to cheer you up,
big brother.

55
00:05:01,541 --> 00:05:03,709
‐ [giggles]

56
00:05:03,709 --> 00:05:05,711
Just send us the usual amount.

57
00:05:05,711 --> 00:05:08,840
‐ I'll pay
at the end of the month.

58
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:10,341
‐ There's so many.

59
00:05:10,341 --> 00:05:11,884
‐ [gasps]

60
00:05:17,056 --> 00:05:18,933
‐ Iolaous.

61
00:05:18,933 --> 00:05:21,227
One. Two. Three.

62
00:05:21,227 --> 00:05:22,979
Four. Four of us.

63
00:05:22,979 --> 00:05:25,523
‐ He can count
all the way up to four now.

64
00:05:25,523 --> 00:05:26,649
‐ We taught him.

65
00:05:26,649 --> 00:05:28,609
He's progressing quite well.

66
00:05:28,609 --> 00:05:29,902
‐ Why did you bring him?

67
00:05:29,902 --> 00:05:31,446
‐ It's not like we can stop him.

68
00:05:31,446 --> 00:05:34,574
‐ Yeah, our ability
just doesn't work on Age.

69
00:05:34,574 --> 00:05:37,034
‐ [growls]

70
00:05:37,034 --> 00:05:41,539
If he didn't have the power of
the Heroic Tribe within him...

71
00:05:41,539 --> 00:05:44,250
You should forget
what you've seen here.

72
00:05:44,250 --> 00:05:45,877
Got it?

73
00:05:47,587 --> 00:05:49,881
‐ Iolaous really likes
Dhianeila.

74
00:05:49,881 --> 00:05:51,924
‐ I said forget it, didn't I?

75
00:05:51,924 --> 00:05:53,676
‐ [chuckles]
Right.

76
00:05:53,676 --> 00:05:55,344
‐ It's certain
that they're aware

77
00:05:55,344 --> 00:05:57,930
we're being pursued
by the Silver Tribe, Captain.

78
00:05:57,930 --> 00:06:01,809
‐ However, Titarros
is a neutral port facility.

79
00:06:01,809 --> 00:06:04,103
As long as we pay,
we shouldn't have a problem

80
00:06:04,103 --> 00:06:05,771
getting supplies.

81
00:06:05,771 --> 00:06:08,274
‐ The problem is the Nodos.

82
00:06:08,274 --> 00:06:10,109
‐ Right.
Although they claim neutrality,

83
00:06:10,109 --> 00:06:12,487
Titarros technically lies
within a territory

84
00:06:12,487 --> 00:06:14,489
controlled by the Silver Tribe.

85
00:06:14,489 --> 00:06:16,699
If they were to find out
that we have the Nodos,

86
00:06:16,699 --> 00:06:18,618
they might alert our enemies.

87
00:06:18,618 --> 00:06:20,912
‐ I just hope
we can keep that under wraps

88
00:06:20,912 --> 00:06:22,455
while we're in harbor.

89
00:06:22,455 --> 00:06:26,083
‐ Keep that boy under wraps?
Not very likely.

90
00:06:26,083 --> 00:06:29,003
There's no telling
what that monkey'll do.

91
00:06:29,003 --> 00:06:30,254
[sighs]

92
00:06:30,254 --> 00:06:31,881
We'll have to ask the princess

93
00:06:31,881 --> 00:06:33,966
to speak with him.

94
00:06:33,966 --> 00:06:39,138
<i>♪ ♪</i>

95
00:06:39,138 --> 00:06:40,973
‐ Hmm?
‐ Huh?

96
00:06:40,973 --> 00:06:45,394
<i>♪ ♪</i>

97
00:06:45,394 --> 00:06:46,646
‐ Don't eat those, okay?

98
00:06:46,646 --> 00:06:48,940
‐ Yes.
They're important for everyone.

99
00:06:48,940 --> 00:06:52,068
‐ That's right.
Those are for everyone.

100
00:06:52,068 --> 00:06:54,195
‐ The "Argonaut" has everyone,
huh?

101
00:06:54,195 --> 00:06:57,240
‐ Poor boy.
He spent his whole life alone.

102
00:06:57,240 --> 00:06:59,158
[device beeps]

103
00:07:00,368 --> 00:07:03,829
‐ Dhianeila and Aneasha.

104
00:07:03,829 --> 00:07:05,331
‐ Here you go, Princess.

105
00:07:05,331 --> 00:07:06,624
‐ Thank you, ladies.

106
00:07:06,624 --> 00:07:08,376
You're always together,
aren't you?

107
00:07:08,376 --> 00:07:10,336
‐ I just hope
those two aren't teaching you

108
00:07:10,336 --> 00:07:11,504
anything weird.

109
00:07:11,504 --> 00:07:13,589
BOTH: [gasping, groaning]

110
00:07:13,589 --> 00:07:14,840
BOTH: [laughing]

111
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:17,718
‐ Now, Age,
we need to talk to you.

112
00:07:17,718 --> 00:07:18,844
‐ About what?

113
00:07:18,844 --> 00:07:19,845
‐ I wanted to let you know

114
00:07:19,845 --> 00:07:20,846
that, soon, we will arrive

115
00:07:20,846 --> 00:07:22,682
at a planet called Titarros.

116
00:07:22,682 --> 00:07:25,351
‐ Dhianeila's planet.
‐ No, no.

117
00:07:25,351 --> 00:07:27,603
We're still quite far
from the Altria system.

118
00:07:27,603 --> 00:07:30,815
We're stopping at Titarros
to replenish our supplies.

119
00:07:30,815 --> 00:07:34,110
I'd like to ask a favor of you
regarding our stop.

120
00:07:34,110 --> 00:07:35,069
While we are on‐world,

121
00:07:35,069 --> 00:07:36,404
I wonder if you would stay here

122
00:07:36,404 --> 00:07:38,281
on the ship.

123
00:07:38,281 --> 00:07:39,198
‐ Huh?

124
00:07:39,198 --> 00:07:40,408
‐ No matter how badly

125
00:07:40,408 --> 00:07:41,784
you wish to go outside
and explore,

126
00:07:41,784 --> 00:07:44,245
you must restrain yourself
and stay in.

127
00:07:44,245 --> 00:07:45,496
‐ But why?

128
00:07:45,496 --> 00:07:47,748
‐ Well‐‐
‐ We wouldn't want to alarm

129
00:07:47,748 --> 00:07:49,583
the people who live there.

130
00:07:49,583 --> 00:07:51,419
‐ Oh...

131
00:07:51,419 --> 00:07:54,088
‐ You know how
Bellcross lives inside of you?

132
00:07:54,088 --> 00:07:56,465
‐ Yeah?
‐ Although you've saved us

133
00:07:56,465 --> 00:07:57,758
time and again,

134
00:07:57,758 --> 00:08:00,720
others may find your existence
frightening.

135
00:08:00,720 --> 00:08:03,389
That's why I think it's best
for everyone involved

136
00:08:03,389 --> 00:08:04,724
if we keep you a secret

137
00:08:04,724 --> 00:08:07,768
and pretend
you're not even on board.

138
00:08:25,828 --> 00:08:27,246
MAN: It's the Iron Tribe

139
00:08:27,246 --> 00:08:29,749
requesting clearance
for a supply stop.

140
00:08:29,749 --> 00:08:31,625
MAN: A ship from Altria
that left the Starway

141
00:08:31,625 --> 00:08:33,127
two cycles ago.

142
00:08:33,127 --> 00:08:36,547
Right now, the Silver Tribe
is pursuing them.

143
00:08:36,547 --> 00:08:38,049
‐ This is a wanted vessel?

144
00:08:38,049 --> 00:08:41,927
That could mean a great deal
of trouble for us, sir.

145
00:08:41,927 --> 00:08:44,513
Shall we alert the Silver Tribe?

146
00:08:44,513 --> 00:08:46,265
‐ That won't be necessary.

147
00:08:46,265 --> 00:08:50,186
You are to follow
normal docking protocol.

148
00:08:50,186 --> 00:08:53,147
‐ We have just been granted
clearance, master.

149
00:08:56,192 --> 00:08:58,653
‐ Here we go.

150
00:08:58,653 --> 00:09:02,823
It's not that easy
to remain neutral, is it?

151
00:09:02,823 --> 00:09:04,283
<i>[classical music]</i>

152
00:09:04,283 --> 00:09:08,037
WOMAN: Topsail sensor array
activation in progress.

153
00:09:09,455 --> 00:09:12,416
Now initiating
ship‐to‐station current link.

154
00:09:12,416 --> 00:09:13,709
Stable.

155
00:09:13,709 --> 00:09:20,716
<i>♪ ♪</i>

156
00:09:22,802 --> 00:09:24,970
Beginning approach.

157
00:09:24,970 --> 00:09:26,806
MAN: Margin of error
on access aisle

158
00:09:26,806 --> 00:09:30,142
.002% and dropping.

159
00:09:30,142 --> 00:09:33,979
<i>♪ ♪</i>

160
00:09:33,979 --> 00:09:37,191
WOMAN: Final docking sequence
in progress.

161
00:09:37,191 --> 00:09:39,068
MAN: Docking automation engaged.

162
00:09:39,068 --> 00:09:42,863
All steps confirmed
and completed.

163
00:09:42,863 --> 00:09:44,907
<i>♪ ♪</i>

164
00:09:44,907 --> 00:09:46,033
‐ Whoa.

165
00:09:46,033 --> 00:09:48,119
WOMAN: Docking complete.

166
00:09:49,662 --> 00:09:52,373
DHIANEILA: I know
this isn't the ideal situation,

167
00:09:52,373 --> 00:09:53,958
but it must be done.

168
00:09:53,958 --> 00:09:55,501
[device beeps]

169
00:09:57,962 --> 00:10:00,339
‐ Princess, we've got a problem.

170
00:10:00,339 --> 00:10:03,342
The authorities wish to perform
an inspection.

171
00:10:03,342 --> 00:10:06,137
DHIANEILA: Does that mean
they found out about Age?

172
00:10:06,137 --> 00:10:08,305
‐ If that were the case,
they wouldn't have allowed us

173
00:10:08,305 --> 00:10:10,266
to dock‐‐
my guess is, the incident

174
00:10:10,266 --> 00:10:12,852
with the Silver Tribe
made them a little nervous.

175
00:10:12,852 --> 00:10:16,188
However, an inspection
will make it difficult for us

176
00:10:16,188 --> 00:10:17,982
to continue hiding him.

177
00:10:17,982 --> 00:10:19,984
DHIANEILA:
Then Age shall wait on Titarros.

178
00:10:19,984 --> 00:10:22,945
‐ What? Let the Nodos
off the "Argonaut"?

179
00:10:22,945 --> 00:10:25,239
‐ Yes.
‐ But...

180
00:10:25,239 --> 00:10:28,743
‐ Relax, Captain.
He won't act out for no reason.

181
00:10:30,745 --> 00:10:32,872
IOLAOUS: You want me
to babysit that monkey?

182
00:10:32,872 --> 00:10:34,915
‐ Because
you can bring him back instantly

183
00:10:34,915 --> 00:10:36,417
if anything goes wrong.

184
00:10:36,417 --> 00:10:38,753
‐ That is true, but‐‐
‐ [clears throat]

185
00:10:38,753 --> 00:10:40,713
The princess chose you.

186
00:10:40,713 --> 00:10:42,715
‐ I understand, Father.

187
00:10:42,715 --> 00:10:44,425
Consider it done.

188
00:10:44,425 --> 00:10:47,136
I do have one request, though.

189
00:10:47,136 --> 00:10:50,389
‐ Here. You need to wear this.
‐ Huh?

190
00:10:50,389 --> 00:10:52,475
‐ Once you have it on,
a team will take you down

191
00:10:52,475 --> 00:10:53,934
to visit the planet.

192
00:10:53,934 --> 00:10:56,687
‐ Huh? Huh?

193
00:10:56,687 --> 00:10:58,481
[laughs]

194
00:10:58,481 --> 00:11:02,443
<i>♪ ♪</i>

195
00:11:02,443 --> 00:11:05,488
[grunting]

196
00:11:07,323 --> 00:11:09,617
I don't like it.
Feels rough.

197
00:11:09,617 --> 00:11:11,911
‐ It looks quite nice on you.

198
00:11:11,911 --> 00:11:14,371
<i>♪ ♪</i>

199
00:11:14,371 --> 00:11:16,415
‐ Thanks, Iolaous.

200
00:11:16,415 --> 00:11:17,833
‐ Why thank me?

201
00:11:17,833 --> 00:11:19,460
‐ You're taking me with you.

202
00:11:19,460 --> 00:11:21,337
‐ Thank Princess Dhianeila.

203
00:11:21,337 --> 00:11:24,256
‐ I want you to follow
all of Iolaous' instructions.

204
00:11:24,256 --> 00:11:25,508
‐ Right.

205
00:11:25,508 --> 00:11:27,676
‐ Starting with this.
‐ Huh?

206
00:11:27,676 --> 00:11:29,970
‐ Now, listen‐‐
my powers of teleportation

207
00:11:29,970 --> 00:11:32,431
won't work on you
unless you allow it,

208
00:11:32,431 --> 00:11:33,599
so if I say "jump,"

209
00:11:33,599 --> 00:11:35,476
you need to shut up and do it.

210
00:11:35,476 --> 00:11:36,435
Got it?

211
00:11:36,435 --> 00:11:38,771
‐ Yep.
‐ Now, hold on.

212
00:11:40,564 --> 00:11:41,816
To the suit!

213
00:11:41,816 --> 00:11:44,026
‐ Looks like
this is harder than a war.

214
00:11:44,026 --> 00:11:46,529
‐ Ridiculous.
‐ [giggles]

215
00:11:46,529 --> 00:11:48,697
‐ Farewell, Princess.

216
00:11:48,697 --> 00:11:50,449
‐ Be good, boys.

217
00:11:50,449 --> 00:11:52,243
‐ Now, jump.

218
00:11:54,578 --> 00:11:57,790
‐ Master,
the inspection pod is here.

219
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:00,709
MOBEEDO: And the data
concerning Planet Olone and Age?

220
00:12:00,709 --> 00:12:02,837
BEE NO BEE:
It's been switched with a decoy.

221
00:12:02,837 --> 00:12:04,129
‐ Good.

222
00:12:04,129 --> 00:12:07,466
Let them inspect
to their heart's content.

223
00:12:18,894 --> 00:12:21,981
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

224
00:12:21,981 --> 00:12:24,817
<i>♪ ♪</i>

225
00:12:24,817 --> 00:12:26,854
‐ I have answered Titarros.

226
00:12:30,781 --> 00:12:33,826
[waves lapping]

227
00:12:40,791 --> 00:12:43,794
[wind howling]

228
00:12:43,794 --> 00:12:45,963
<i>[ethereal music]</i>

229
00:12:45,963 --> 00:12:50,509
‐ I have found him, Yuty La.

230
00:12:50,509 --> 00:12:55,264
<i>♪ ♪</i>

231
00:12:55,264 --> 00:12:57,182
‐ He must be tested.

232
00:12:57,182 --> 00:12:59,143
‐ I do hope the fifth is nice.

233
00:12:59,143 --> 00:13:00,686
‐ According
to the Golden Tribe's

234
00:13:00,686 --> 00:13:01,562
ancient prophecy,

235
00:13:01,562 --> 00:13:03,188
the fifth Nodos is controlled

236
00:13:03,188 --> 00:13:04,398
by the Iron Tribe,

237
00:13:04,398 --> 00:13:07,026
and he fights
against the other Nodos.

238
00:13:07,026 --> 00:13:08,694
‐ What are you saying?

239
00:13:08,694 --> 00:13:11,447
‐ If he doesn't wish
to join us‐‐

240
00:13:11,447 --> 00:13:13,365
‐ He dies.
KARKINOS: No.

241
00:13:13,365 --> 00:13:15,367
We should talk to him first.

242
00:13:15,367 --> 00:13:18,162
If that fails,
then we'll force him to submit.

243
00:13:18,162 --> 00:13:21,373
‐ We should not allow the one
who disobeys the Silver Tribe

244
00:13:21,373 --> 00:13:22,958
to remain alive.

245
00:13:22,958 --> 00:13:25,794
Mehitak, you will go.

246
00:13:25,794 --> 00:13:28,422
‐ I don't like to fight.

247
00:13:28,422 --> 00:13:30,424
‐ Then I will go.

248
00:13:32,301 --> 00:13:35,179
I'd like to meet the fifth.

249
00:13:39,558 --> 00:13:41,185
‐ As you wish, Karkinos,

250
00:13:41,185 --> 00:13:43,312
but don't underestimate him.

251
00:13:43,312 --> 00:13:44,897
‐ Don't worry.

252
00:13:44,897 --> 00:13:46,690
I won't.

253
00:13:49,318 --> 00:13:51,278
Lecty, come.

254
00:13:54,615 --> 00:14:01,664
<i>♪ ♪</i>

255
00:14:13,801 --> 00:14:16,929
[vehicles roaring and whooshing]

256
00:14:21,934 --> 00:14:23,185
‐ Heh.

257
00:14:27,272 --> 00:14:29,441
[laughs]

258
00:14:30,526 --> 00:14:31,985
MAN: Are you saying
we should detain

259
00:14:31,985 --> 00:14:34,279
the Iron Tribe's ship illegally?

260
00:14:34,279 --> 00:14:36,407
‐ With all due respect,
the planet Titarros

261
00:14:36,407 --> 00:14:38,283
is a neutral supply station.

262
00:14:38,283 --> 00:14:40,661
We can't hold them
without a reason.

263
00:14:40,661 --> 00:14:42,913
‐ A reason?

264
00:14:46,333 --> 00:14:48,919
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

265
00:14:50,921 --> 00:14:53,924
IOLAOUS: Hey, stop pulling me!
What is it now?

266
00:14:56,552 --> 00:14:59,847
I wish
I was getting shot at right now.

267
00:14:59,847 --> 00:15:02,099
Hey!

268
00:15:02,099 --> 00:15:03,517
‐ Hmm?
‐ Again?

269
00:15:03,517 --> 00:15:05,644
There's still food
in your mouth.

270
00:15:09,189 --> 00:15:12,234
All right,
but this is the last time.

271
00:15:12,234 --> 00:15:13,277
Let's go.

272
00:15:13,277 --> 00:15:14,486
‐ Yeah!

273
00:15:14,486 --> 00:15:16,238
‐ Is eating
all you ever think about?

274
00:15:16,238 --> 00:15:18,282
‐ Mm‐hmm.

275
00:15:23,245 --> 00:15:24,496
LECTY: Be careful.

276
00:15:24,496 --> 00:15:26,498
KARKINOS: My only intent
is to meet him.

277
00:15:26,498 --> 00:15:28,625
That's all.

278
00:15:31,503 --> 00:15:33,005
DHIANEILA: Captain.

279
00:15:33,005 --> 00:15:35,632
Something is looking for Age.

280
00:15:35,632 --> 00:15:37,009
‐ Something?

281
00:15:37,009 --> 00:15:38,802
DHIANEILA: I don't know
exactly what it is,

282
00:15:38,802 --> 00:15:40,888
but it's very strong.

283
00:15:40,888 --> 00:15:42,431
‐ This can't be good.

284
00:15:42,431 --> 00:15:45,100
And I'm afraid
there's more bad news.

285
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:47,436
Titarros just announced
that they're going to detain

286
00:15:47,436 --> 00:15:49,021
the ship.

287
00:15:49,021 --> 00:15:51,440
The Silver Tribe is behind this.

288
00:15:51,440 --> 00:15:54,359
We need to get Iolaous and Age
back to the ship and leave

289
00:15:54,359 --> 00:15:56,278
while we can still fight our way
out of this.

290
00:15:56,278 --> 00:15:58,822
DHIANEILA: No.
Violence may not be necessary.

291
00:15:58,822 --> 00:16:00,949
Please try
to negotiate with them.

292
00:16:00,949 --> 00:16:03,035
‐ What?
DHIANEILA: Try.

293
00:16:03,035 --> 00:16:05,037
It seems
their hand is being forced

294
00:16:05,037 --> 00:16:07,206
in this matter.

295
00:16:16,548 --> 00:16:18,550
‐ Is Iolaous afraid of Age?

296
00:16:18,550 --> 00:16:20,385
‐ Afraid? That's preposterous.

297
00:16:20,385 --> 00:16:22,304
I'm not afraid of anything.

298
00:16:22,304 --> 00:16:24,181
‐ Heh.

299
00:16:25,724 --> 00:16:28,018
‐ Why would you ask me that?

300
00:16:28,018 --> 00:16:29,520
‐ Because you said it's better

301
00:16:29,520 --> 00:16:32,231
if there's no Age
on the "Argonaut."

302
00:16:34,066 --> 00:16:36,443
There's so much
that Age really likes.

303
00:16:36,443 --> 00:16:38,153
Age likes Iolaous.

304
00:16:38,153 --> 00:16:40,322
Age likes the "Argonaut" too.

305
00:16:40,322 --> 00:16:43,450
And Dhianeila's voice
is like a warm light.

306
00:16:43,450 --> 00:16:45,410
Aneasha is the morning air.

307
00:16:45,410 --> 00:16:48,080
Tail and Mail
are both beautiful clouds.

308
00:16:48,080 --> 00:16:49,915
‐ Then I suppose
their mean older brother

309
00:16:49,915 --> 00:16:52,918
would be something like
a big melancholy rain cloud.

310
00:16:52,918 --> 00:16:54,336
‐ [laughs]
Iolaous is‐‐

311
00:16:54,336 --> 00:16:55,629
[device beeps]

312
00:16:55,629 --> 00:16:58,799
IOLAOUS:
It's the emergency signal.

313
00:16:58,799 --> 00:17:00,008
We got to go.

314
00:17:06,849 --> 00:17:07,891
[woman screams]

315
00:17:10,978 --> 00:17:12,604
Age!

316
00:17:17,276 --> 00:17:19,611
MAN: Please accept
my humble apologies for this,

317
00:17:19,611 --> 00:17:21,405
Princess Dhianeila.

318
00:17:21,405 --> 00:17:23,574
‐ There is no need for that,
Your Excellency.

319
00:17:23,574 --> 00:17:25,951
I am keenly aware
of your situation.

320
00:17:25,951 --> 00:17:27,953
However,
I can't comply with your demand

321
00:17:27,953 --> 00:17:29,705
to hand over our ship.

322
00:17:29,705 --> 00:17:31,206
‐ Your Highness,
I must be frank.

323
00:17:31,206 --> 00:17:33,417
It's dangerous
to oppose the Silver Tribe.

324
00:17:33,417 --> 00:17:36,211
You'll have no chance
of escaping their wrath.

325
00:17:36,211 --> 00:17:38,046
‐ I realize this,
but no matter what,

326
00:17:38,046 --> 00:17:40,549
we must return home
our last hope.

327
00:17:40,549 --> 00:17:42,259
‐ What hope?

328
00:17:42,259 --> 00:17:44,261
‐ I speak
of the savior of mankind,

329
00:17:44,261 --> 00:17:46,972
left behind by the Golden Tribe.

330
00:17:46,972 --> 00:17:48,765
‐ According to the prophecy,

331
00:17:48,765 --> 00:17:51,018
mankind's only hope
to survive extinction

332
00:17:51,018 --> 00:17:55,147
is a child possessing
the Heroic Tribe within.

333
00:17:55,147 --> 00:17:56,815
That can't be.

334
00:17:56,815 --> 00:17:58,108
It's here?

335
00:17:58,108 --> 00:18:01,153
<i>[rousing music]</i>

336
00:18:01,153 --> 00:18:04,990
<i>♪ ♪</i>

337
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:07,492
Is this true,
Princess Dhianeila?

338
00:18:07,492 --> 00:18:11,413
Did you acquire a Nodos
and then bring it to our planet?

339
00:18:11,413 --> 00:18:13,665
‐ We have faith
in the Golden Tribe's prophecy

340
00:18:13,665 --> 00:18:15,584
of the fifth Nodos, and at last,

341
00:18:15,584 --> 00:18:17,878
we have the power
to resist our annihilation

342
00:18:17,878 --> 00:18:19,463
by the Silver Tribe.

343
00:18:19,463 --> 00:18:21,131
Mark my words, Excellency,

344
00:18:21,131 --> 00:18:22,841
we shall never give in.

345
00:18:22,841 --> 00:18:24,343
‐ Are you threatening
to attack us

346
00:18:24,343 --> 00:18:26,720
if we don't approve
your departure?

347
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:31,683
‐ We will depart
the moment that we are ready.

348
00:18:31,683 --> 00:18:34,728
MAN: The Daedalus aren't
a particularly warlike people.

349
00:18:34,728 --> 00:18:37,606
Most likely, they'll let us go
without incident.

350
00:18:37,606 --> 00:18:39,691
MAN: In essence,
the princess' threats

351
00:18:39,691 --> 00:18:41,985
make this
an invasion of Titarros.

352
00:18:41,985 --> 00:18:44,404
That isn't our way.

353
00:18:44,404 --> 00:18:45,864
‐ No, it's not,

354
00:18:45,864 --> 00:18:48,200
but rarely will she compromise.

355
00:18:48,200 --> 00:18:50,410
I think
that's what we need right now.

356
00:18:50,410 --> 00:18:54,539
Her unwavering principle
gives us the strength.

357
00:18:54,539 --> 00:18:55,916
Got that?

358
00:18:57,459 --> 00:19:00,045
The ball is in our court,
so to speak.

359
00:19:00,045 --> 00:19:01,838
We'll depart immediately.

360
00:19:01,838 --> 00:19:03,048
BOTH: Yes, sir.

361
00:19:03,048 --> 00:19:04,758
MAN: That wasn't a negotiation.

362
00:19:04,758 --> 00:19:06,385
That was just a threat!

363
00:19:06,385 --> 00:19:08,428
Absolutely unacceptable.

364
00:19:08,428 --> 00:19:10,555
MAN: Calm down.
Everything is fine.

365
00:19:10,555 --> 00:19:11,848
‐ Huh?

366
00:19:11,848 --> 00:19:13,475
‐ This is good for us.

367
00:19:13,475 --> 00:19:15,727
If this elicits
a rebuke from the Silver Tribe,

368
00:19:15,727 --> 00:19:18,605
we can say we were helpless
against hostile intent.

369
00:19:18,605 --> 00:19:19,564
See?

370
00:19:19,564 --> 00:19:22,609
Let them be on their merry way.

371
00:19:22,609 --> 00:19:24,987
‐ Understood.

372
00:19:24,987 --> 00:19:29,574
Princess Dhianeila,
we can't find Age anywhere.

373
00:19:29,574 --> 00:19:31,952
DHIANEILA: I see him.
He is...

374
00:19:37,124 --> 00:19:40,210
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

375
00:19:44,548 --> 00:19:47,551
<i>♪ ♪</i>

376
00:19:51,930 --> 00:19:54,599
‐ I am here to meet the fifth.

377
00:19:54,599 --> 00:19:56,310
My name is Karkinos.

378
00:19:56,310 --> 00:19:57,602
‐ I'm Age.

379
00:19:57,602 --> 00:19:59,688
‐ Come with me, Age.

380
00:20:02,607 --> 00:20:04,526
WOMAN: I just sent you
Age's coordinates.

381
00:20:04,526 --> 00:20:06,945
IOLAOUS: I'm sorry.
WOMAN: There's no time to lose.

382
00:20:06,945 --> 00:20:08,572
Something big is after him.

383
00:20:08,572 --> 00:20:10,615
Bring him back immediately.

384
00:20:10,615 --> 00:20:12,117
‐ Understood.

385
00:20:12,117 --> 00:20:15,954
<i>♪ ♪</i>

386
00:20:15,954 --> 00:20:18,415
‐ We both possess
the Heroic Tribe within.

387
00:20:18,415 --> 00:20:20,417
There's no need for a fight.

388
00:20:20,417 --> 00:20:22,210
‐ My dad told me...

389
00:20:22,210 --> 00:20:25,213
one, two, three, four.

390
00:20:25,213 --> 00:20:29,009
All four of them
need to be destroyed.

391
00:20:30,927 --> 00:20:33,096
‐ What the‐‐
who is that?

392
00:20:33,096 --> 00:20:35,724
‐ He's just like Age.

393
00:20:35,724 --> 00:20:37,309
‐ Hey!

394
00:20:37,309 --> 00:20:39,353
‐ Ah!

395
00:20:45,400 --> 00:20:46,985
‐ No! Age!

396
00:20:57,829 --> 00:21:01,541
<i>♪ ♪</i>

397
00:21:01,541 --> 00:21:05,921
DHIANEILA: Age... what is it
you're trying to fight?

398
00:21:05,921 --> 00:21:08,090
And why?

399
00:21:09,132 --> 00:21:10,509
[gasps]

400
00:21:10,509 --> 00:21:11,802
‐ Detecting several vessels

401
00:21:11,802 --> 00:21:13,053
coming in at warp!

402
00:21:13,053 --> 00:21:15,013
‐ What now?

403
00:21:18,892 --> 00:21:20,102
‐ They're anthills.

404
00:21:20,102 --> 00:21:21,812
‐ Did the Daedalus send them?

405
00:21:21,812 --> 00:21:23,855
DHIANEILA: They know nothing
of this, Captain.

406
00:21:23,855 --> 00:21:25,190
‐ They don't?

407
00:21:25,190 --> 00:21:26,358
Then that means...

408
00:21:26,358 --> 00:21:27,776
DHIANEILA: Yes.

409
00:21:27,776 --> 00:21:30,195
MAN: It's
the Bronze Tribe's anthills!

410
00:21:30,195 --> 00:21:31,488
‐ Uh, sir?

411
00:21:31,488 --> 00:21:34,408
‐ They were testing us
this whole time.

412
00:21:34,408 --> 00:21:35,951
‐ Testing us?

413
00:21:35,951 --> 00:21:38,245
‐ And we failed to obey.

414
00:21:38,245 --> 00:21:39,996
‐ We didn't detain a ship
illegally.

415
00:21:39,996 --> 00:21:43,375
That's all.
It would've led to violence!

416
00:21:43,375 --> 00:21:47,003
‐ They instructed us
to detain them!

417
00:21:48,213 --> 00:21:50,799
‐ They would kill us all
for that?

418
00:21:50,799 --> 00:21:51,925
‐ That's right.

419
00:21:51,925 --> 00:21:54,386
Every last one of us.

420
00:21:54,386 --> 00:21:55,971
DHIANEILA:
The Silver Tribe is willing

421
00:21:55,971 --> 00:21:59,349
to destroy the entire planet
to get to us!

422
00:21:59,349 --> 00:22:06,356
<i>♪ ♪</i>

423
00:22:14,322 --> 00:22:21,329
<i>♪ ♪</i>

424
00:22:32,741 --> 00:22:35,093
<i>["Azurite" by Tae Urakabe]</i>

425
00:22:35,093 --> 00:22:38,180
[woman singing in Japanese]

426
00:23:42,160 --> 00:23:45,622
What lives within him
is called Lernaea.

427
00:23:45,622 --> 00:23:48,208
It turned Titarros
into a battleground.

428
00:23:48,208 --> 00:23:51,419
Next time on "Heroic Age,"
episode five, "The Nodos."

